    "privileged_info_summary": "The border_stroke task (border_stroke@1) uses GIMP 2.10 in the example.gimp_env@0.1 environment with an 90-second timeout and max 7 steps. Data is sourced from real Unsplash images (photo IDs 1506905925346 and 1518837695005) with a synthetic fallback if downloads fail. The verifier checks four criteria: edge darkening ≥15%, uniform borders (darkening std <0.1), center preservation >95% (mean pixel diff <10/255), and border detection. Pass threshold is 75% (3 of 4 criteria). Edge analysis examines 30-pixel border regions, center analysis excludes outer 50-pixel margins. Recommended stroke width is 15-20 pixels. Export is automated to bordered_image.jpg. All numerical thresholds and verification logic were independently verified against the verifier.py source code.",
